  "description": "Debuted on the market in the winter of 2020, the refrigerator of the German manufacturer Liebherr represents the Comfort line and belongs to the advanced models. The refrigerator compartment and freezer, located below, are complemented by the so-called BioFresh zero chamber with a pair of drawers isolated from other shelves. Their total capacity is 94 liters, which will allow you to store here both meat or fish, as well as vegetables and fruits. The Liebherr CBNbs 4835 refrigerator has a useful volume of 343 liters, of which 101 liters are in the freezer. It provides 3 drawers and is able to freeze up to 16 kg of food per day. In the event of a power outage, the unit will keep cold for at least 24 hours. The 148-litre refrigerator compartment (this is the volume without the freshness zone) has a deodorizer that removes unpleasant odours, and 3 of the 4 shelves can be adjusted in height. The important advantages of the model include quiet operation (up to 34 dB), support for the NoFrost automatic defrost system in all compartments and the presence of touch-sensitive internal control (2.4-inch display). Another plus is economical energy consumption at the level of 186 kWh per year (class A ++).",
